parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Steering Column Shift Lock Mechanism
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty steering column shift lock mechanism can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park, making it difficult or impossible to shift into gear, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle will not shift from park
requiring manual intervention to unlock the shift lever
and may cause difficulty or impossibility to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Malfunctioning Heating and Air Conditioning System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning heating and air conditioning system can cause reduced visibility due to fogging or misting of the windshield, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in rainy or humid conditions.
symptoms: The heater blows cold air instead of hot air
making it difficult to defog the windshield
and reducing visibility while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended window roll-down can cause safety risks, especially in extreme weather conditions, and may lead to theft or property damage.
symptoms: Windows roll down unexpectedly
even when the vehicle is parked and unattended
and may occur repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Engine Manifold and Catalytic Converter Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked engine manifold and catalytic converter can cause excessive oil consumption, smoke emission, and loud vibrating noises, which can lead to engine damage, decreased performance, and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: Loud vibrating noise coming from the front of the vehicle
smoke emission from under the hood
excessive oil consumption
increased oil usage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the exhaust system can cause the tailpipe to fall off, posing a safety threat as it can become a road hazard, and potentially damage other vital components like brake lines and tires, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The tailpipe corrodes and falls off
the exhaust system leaks
the vehicle emits loud noises
the vehicle's performance is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system overflow can cause fuel spills, which can lead to fires, and potentially cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel overflows every time the vehicle is filled
even when the tank is empty
fuel spills onto the ground
the fuel pump shuts off prematurely.
